      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "The constitutive model employs a bilinear isotropic hardening representation of Ti-6Al-4V. While adequate for stiffness prediction, the model form does not capture anisotropic texture effects arising from the machining process of non-cannulated screws, contributing to the observed yield force over-prediction (E/uval = 2.34). The contact formulation uses a penalty method with a fixed friction coefficient of 0.2; sensitivity to friction coefficient variation was not fully characterized. At modelRiskLevel 3, Gradation 3 is required for model form, but only Gradation 2 is achieved given the uncharacterized anisotropy and contact sensitivity. This shortfall is a primary driver of the Not-accepted decision.",
