      "rationale": "Nominal Ti-6Al-4V material properties sourced from ASTM B265 and supplier certificates of conformance. Geometric inputs derived from nominal CAD with dimensional tolerances applied as ±0.05 mm on rod diameter. However, actual as-built dimensions of the N=11 test constructs were not measured and incorporated individually; instead, nominal dimensions were used for all specimens. This input fidelity gap — particularly relevant for the non-cannulated screw thread geometry — is a contributing factor to the yield force prediction shortfall. At modelRiskLevel 3, Gradation 3 is required, demanding specimen-specific or statistically characterized inputs; only Gradation 2 is achieved. This shortfall jointly drives the Not-accepted decision.",
